cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper focuses on analyzing and evaluating handwriting in patients with Parkinson's disease using various features and classifiers. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves the interaction between the patient and the computer-based analysis of their handwriting. The use of kinematic, geometrical, and non-linear features also suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques are employed. Additionally, the use of classifiers such as K-nearest neighbors, support vector machines, and random forest indicates that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SD).
